      "genre": "Drama",
      "type": "MOVIE",
      "status": "APPROVED",
      "createdAt": "2024-12-12T14:23:14.000Z"
    },
    {
      "title": "Lucky Bhaskar Review: When Luck and Strategy Makes Life Interesting",
      "slug": "lucky-bhaskar-when-luck-meets-strategy",
      "content": "<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"orientation\":\"vertical\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"0.8\"}}} -->\n<p style=\"line-height: 0.8;\">Movie Name: <strong>Lucky Bhaskar</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"0.8\"}}} -->\n<p style=\"line-height: 0.8;\">Cast: <strong>Dilquer Salmann, Meenakshi Chaudhary</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"0.8\"}}} -->\n<p style=\"line-height: 0.8;\">Director:<strong> Venky Atluri</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"0.8\"}}} -->\n<p style=\"line-height: 0.8;\">Genre: <strong>Crime Drama</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"0.8\"}}} -->\n<p style=\"line-height: 0.8;\">Available on: <strong>Netflix</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":904,\"width\":\"204px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img class=\"wp-image-904\" style=\"width: 204px; height: auto;\" src=\"https://cinebuffs.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/3and5-stars.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Set against the backdrop of the early 90s and the infamous Harshad Mehta case, this film delivers a compelling story that captures the struggles and ambitions of the common man. The protagonist, Bhaskar, portrayed brilliantly by Dulquer Salmaan, is a lower-middle-class family man burdened with responsibilities. His desperate shortcut to earn money may be slightly illegal, but it’s portrayed in a way that feels harmless—at least initially.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bhaskar’s journey into the world of gambling is both fascinating and cautionary. Once he gets a taste of easy money, stopping becomes an impossible task. His eventual decision to take one last big risk and secure his future adds an intriguing layer to the narrative. The screenplay is tightly woven, and the execution is commendable, keeping the audience hooked from start to finish.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1001,\"width\":\"680px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img class=\"wp-image-1001\" style=\"width: 680px; height: auto;\" src=\"https://cinebuffs.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/jul-2024-pics-film-lucky-baskhar-5787-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bhaskar’s character is highly relatable, with his desperation and misery resonating deeply. His intelligence and calculated decisions, akin to a seasoned gambler, add depth and complexity to his persona. The ending, while simple, is satisfying and reflective of Bhaskar’s growth and understanding of his own circumstances.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The film does an excellent job balancing crime, drama, and human emotions, making Bhaskar’s journey both engaging and thought-provoking. It’s a must-watch for fans of crime dramas and anyone looking for a story that blends relatability with high stakes. This movie is a testament to the fact that sometimes, intelligence and timing are just as important as luck.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->",
